# SARS-CoV-2 Homo sapiens
The SARS-CoV-2 Homo sapiens nucleotide sequence represents the complete or partial genetic material of the SARS-CoV-2 virus isolated from infected human hosts. SARS-CoV-2 is an RNA virus responsible for the COVID-19 pandemic and belongs to the coronavirus family.

This sequence contains important viral genes involved in replication, host-cell attachment, and immune system interaction, including the spike glycoprotein region. It is widely used in genomic surveillance, mutation analysis, vaccine research, and comparative genomics studies.

The sequence is highly valuable for bioinformatics applications such as multiple sequence alignment, phylogenetic tree construction, protein translation, variant detection, and evolutionary analysis. Researchers also use it to study viral transmission patterns and emerging mutations across different populations.
